  "title": "Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p>On behalf of our client, who is an Original Equipment Maker (OEM)  in the built environment space, we are looking for a Service Engineer with the following details :</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Description</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To lead a team of technicians to maintain a portfolio of equipment in servicing, repair, modifications, and callback.</li>\n  <li>Customers' point of contact in terms of feedback or request pertaining to equipment, resolving issues, reports, etc to achieve customer satisfaction.</li>\n  <li>Monitor equipment performance and handle problematic lifts &amp; escalators to achieve targets as well as continual improvement</li>\n  <li>Plan, Implement, Monitor &amp; Control the progress of chargeable, non-chargeable works, monthly servicing schedules, and callback roster</li>\n  <li>Provide leadership, technical guidance, and support to subordinates.</li>\n  <li>Obtain required materials/resources for works as required</li>\n  <li>Prepare and conduct training for maintenance field staff with monitoring to ensure MIP/Best Practices are properly implemented</li>\n  <li>Complete office administrative works as required.</li>\n  <li>To communicate with inter-department staff for solutions &amp; resolve issues</li>\n  <li>Report and assist Section Head on operations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Requirement</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Mechanic/Electrical/Mechatronic Engineering</li>\n  <li>With at least 2-3 years of experience in a supervisory /team lead role</li>\n  <li>To be 24/7 operationally ready to attend to issues (rostered)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA registration : 22C0971 | EA License : R21101298</p>",
